CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, February 14, 1938, pg. 22, reads: "Lena Horne Jones, the glamourous former radio, nite club and stage star, selected to co-star with Ralph Cooper in first all-colored musical revue having a farewell chat with her father Teddy Horne (facing camera) and husband Louis Jones."
TitMainTitle: Lena Horne holding Persian lamb coat, with her father Teddy Horne, husband Louis Jones, and unknown man, standing beside flight information board at Allegheny County airport
